import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='price', hue='symbol', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of stock prices over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Stock Symbol')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='price', bins=30, kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['price'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of stock prices?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Stock Prices")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    avg_stock_price = data.groupby('symbol')['price'].mean().reset_index()
    
    chart = sns.barplot(x='symbol', y='price', data=avg_stock_price)
    plt.title('What is the average stock price for each symbol?', wrap=True)
    plt.ylabel('Average Stock Price')
    plt.xlabel('Symbol')
    
    for index, row in avg_stock_price.iterrows():
        chart.text(index, row['price'], f"{row['price']:.2f}", color='black', ha='center')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
